g1702.definition: [ἐμπαίζω] from {{g1722}} and {{g3815}}; to jeer at, i.e. deride

g1703.definition: [ἐμπαίκτης] from {{g1702}}; a derider, i.e. (by implication) a false teacher

g1704.definition: [ἐμπεριπατέω] from {{g1722}} and {{g4043}}; to perambulate on a place, i.e. (figuratively) to be occupied among persons

g1705.definition: [ἐμπίπλημι]   or ἐμπλήθωfrom {{g1722}} and the base of {{g4118}};to fill in (up), i.e. (by implication) to satisfy (literally or figuratively)

g1706.definition: [ἐμπίπτω] from {{g1722}} and {{g4098}}; to fall on, i.e. (literally) to be entrapped by, or (figuratively) be overwhelmed with

g1707.definition: [ἐμπλέκω] from {{g1722}} and {{g4120}}; to entwine, i.e. (figuratively) involve with

g1708.definition: [ἐμπλοκή] from {{g1707}}; elaborate braiding of the hair

g1709.definition: [ἐμπνέω] from {{g1722}} and {{g4154}}; to inhale, i.e. (figuratively) to be animated by (bent upon)

g1710.definition: [ἐμπορεύομαι] from {{g1722}} and {{g4198}}; to travel in (a country as a pedlar), i.e. (by implication) to trade

g1713.definition: [ἔμπορος] from {{g1722}} and the base of {{g4198}}; a (wholesale) tradesman

g1714.definition: [ἐμπρήθω] from {{g1722}} and πρήθω (to blow a flame); to enkindle, i.e. set on fire

g1715.definition: [ἔμπροσθεν] from {{g1722}} and {{g4314}}; in front of (in place (literally or figuratively) or time)

g1716.definition: [ἐμπτύω] from {{g1722}} and {{g4429}}; to spit at or on

g1717.definition: [ἐμφανής] from a compound of {{g1722}} and {{g5316}}; apparent in self

g1718.definition: [ἐμφανίζω] from {{g1717}}; to exhibit (in person) or disclose (by words)

g1719.definition: [ἔμφοβος] from {{g1722}} and {{g5401}}; in fear, i.e. alarmed

g1720.definition: [ἐμφυσάω] from {{g1722}} and φυσάω (to puff) (compare {{g5453}}); to blow at or on

g1721.definition: [ἔμφυτος] from {{g1722}} and a derivative of {{g5453}}; implanted (figuratively)

g1722.definition: [ἐν] a primary preposition denoting (fixed) position (in place, time or state), and (by implication) instrumentality (medially or constructively), i.e. a relation of rest (intermediate between {{g1519}} and {{g1537}}); "in," at, (up-)on, by, etc. Often used in compounds, with substantially the same import; rarely with verbs of motion, and then not to indicate direction, except (elliptically) by a separate (and different) preposition.

g1723.definition: [ἐναγκαλίζομαι] from {{g1722}} and a derivative of {{g43}}; to take in one's arms, i.e. embrace

g1724.definition: [ἐνάλιος] from {{g1722}} and {{g251}}; in the sea, i.e. marine

g1725.definition: [ἔναντι] from {{g1722}} and {{g473}}; in front (i.e. figuratively, presence) of

g1726.definition: [ἐναντίον] neuter of {{g1727}}; (adverbially) in the presence (view) of

g1729.definition: [ἐνδεής] from a compound of {{g1722}} and {{g1210}} (in the sense of lacking); deficient in

g1731.definition: [ἐνδείκνυμι] from {{g1722}} and {{g1166}}; to indicate (by word or act)

g1733.definition: [ἕνδεκα] from (the neuter of) {{g1520}} and {{g1176}}; one and ten, i.e. eleven

g1735.definition: [ἐνδέχεται] third person singular present of a compound of {{g1722}} and {{g1209}}; (impersonally) it is accepted in, i.e. admitted (possible)

g1736.definition: [ἐνδημέω] from a compound of {{g1722}} and {{g1218}}; to be in one's own country, i.e. home (figuratively)

g1737.definition: [ἐνδιδύσκω] a prolonged form of {{g1746}}; to invest (with a garment)

g1738.definition: [ἔνδικος] from {{g1722}} and {{g1349}}; in the right, i.e. equitable

g1739.definition: [ἐνδόμησις] from a compound of {{g1722}} and a derivative of the base of {{g1218}}; a housing in (residence), i.e. structure

g1741.definition: [ἔνδοξος] from {{g1722}} and {{g1391}}; in glory, i.e. splendid, (figuratively) noble

g1744.definition: [ἐνδύνω] from {{g1772}} and {{g1416}}; to sink (by implication, wrap (compare {{g1746}}) on, i.e. (figuratively) sneak

g1746.definition: [ἐνδύω] from {{g1722}} and {{g1416}} (in the sense of sinking into a garment); to invest with clothing (literally or figuratively)

g1747.definition: [ἐνέδρα] feminine from {{g1722}} and the base of {{g1476}}; an ambuscade, i.e. (figuratively) murderous purpose See also {{g1749}}.

g1748.definition: [ἐνεδρεύω] from {{g1747}}; to lurk, i.e. (figuratively) plot assassination

g1749.definition: [ἔνεδρον] neuter of the same as {{g1747}}; an ambush, i.e. (figuratively) murderous design

g1750.definition: [ἐνειλέω] from {{g1772}} and the base of {{g1507}}; to enwrap

g1751.definition: [ἔνειμι] from {{g1772}} and {{g1510}}; to be within (neuter participle plural) See also {{g1762}}.

g1752.definition: [ἕνεκα]   or ἕνεκεν  or εἵνεκενof uncertain affinity; on account of

g1757.definition: [ἐνευλογέω] from {{g1722}} and {{g2127}}; to confer a benefit on

g1758.definition: [ἐνέχω] from {{g1722}} and {{g2192}}; to hold in or upon, i.e. ensnare; by implication, to keep a grudge

g1759.definition: [ἐνθάδε] from a prolonged form of {{g1722}}; properly, within, i.e. (of place) here, hither

g1760.definition: [ἐνθυμέομαι] from a compound of {{g1722}} and {{g2372}}; to be inspirited, i.e. ponder

g1762.definition: [ἔνι] contraction for the third person singular present indicative of {{g1751}}; impersonally, there is in or among

g1763.definition: [ἐνιαυτός] prolongation from a primary ἔνος (a year); a year

g1764.definition: [ἐνίστημι] from {{g1722}} and {{g2476}}; to place on hand, i.e. (reflexively) impend, (participle) be instant

g1765.definition: [ἐνισχύω] from {{g1722}} and {{g2480}}; to invigorate (transitively or reflexively)

g1768.definition: [ἐννενηκονταεννέα] from a (tenth) multiple of {{g1767}} and {{g1767}} itself; ninety-nine

g1769.definition: [ἐννεός] from {{g1770}}; dumb (as making signs), i.e. silent from astonishment

g1770.definition: [ἐννεύω] from {{g1722}} and {{g3506}}; to nod at, i.e. beckon or communicate by gesture

g1771.definition: [ἔννοια] from a compound of {{g1722}} and {{g3563}}; thoughtfulness, i.e. moral understanding

g1772.definition: [ἔννομος] from {{g1722}} and {{g3551}}; (subjectively) legal, or (objectively) subject to

g1773.definition: [ἔννυχον] neuter of a compound of {{g1722}} and {{g3571}}; (adverbially) by night

g1776.definition: [ἐνοχλέω] from {{g1722}} and {{g3791}}; to crowd in, i.e. (figuratively) to annoy

g1777.definition: [ἔνοχος] from {{g1758}}; liable to (a condition, penalty or imputation)

g1778.definition: [ἔνταλμα] from {{g1781}}; an injunction, i.e. religious precept

g1779.definition: [ἐνταφιάζω] from a compound of {{g1722}} and {{g5028}}; to inswathe with cerements for interment

g1781.definition: [ἐντέλλομαι] from {{g1722}} and the base of {{g5056}}; to enjoin

g1782.definition: [ἐντεῦθεν] from the same as {{g1759}}; hence (literally or figuratively); (repeated) on both sides

g1785.definition: [ἐντολή] from {{g1781}}; injunction, i.e. an authoritative prescription

g1788.definition: [ἐντρέπω] from {{g1722}} and the base of {{g5157}}; to invert, i.e. (figuratively and reflexively) in a good sense, to respect; or in a bad one, to confound

g1793.definition: [ἐντυγχάνω] from {{g1722}} and {{g5177}}; to chance upon, i.e. (by implication) confer with; by extension to entreat (in favor or against)

g1794.definition: [ἐντυλίσσω] from {{g1722}} and τυλίσσω (to twist; probably akin to {{g1507}}); to entwine, i.e. wind up in

g1795.definition: [ἐντυπόω] from {{g1722}} and a derivative of {{g5179}}; to enstamp, i.e. engrave

g1798.definition: [ἐνύπνιον] from {{g1722}} and {{g5258}}; something seen in sleep, i.e. a dream (vision in a dream)

g1799.definition: [ἐνώπιον] neuter of a compound of {{g1722}} and a derivative of {{g3700}}; in the face of (literally or figuratively)

g1800.definition: [Ἐνώς] of Hebrew origin ({{h583}}); Enos (i.e. Enosh), a patriarch
